A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Natural Resources – State Boat Act – Alterations
3 FOR the purpose of altering the definition of “personal watercraft” and “personal flotation
4 device” for purposes of the State Boat Act; repealing the definition of “Class A vessel”
5 as it applies to the rental of livery vessels; repealing the definition of “personal
6 flotation device” as it applies to certain waterskiing restrictions; repealing certain
7 advertising and public hearing requirements for proposed regulations implementing
8 the State Boat Act; increasing the funding threshold for certain projects financed by
9 the Waterway Improvement Fund; altering the fees for manufacturer and dealer
10 licenses, certificates of number, Maryland use stickers, and the issuance of
11 certificates of title, transfer of title, or duplicate or corrected certificates of title;
12 authorizing the owner of certain vessels to apply to the Department of Natural
13 Resources for a nonmotorized vessel decal; authorizing the Department to establish
14 or alter certain speed zones or restricted areas by public notice; altering the
15 requirements for a personal flotation device worn by a child in certain vessels; and
16 generally relating to the State Boat Act.
